description: Beacon v2 GenomicVariation see also https://www.ga4gh.org/product/categorical-variation-catvar/
A unique identifier maintained by an authoritative database that represents a genetic variation. E.g. 20:2447955..2447958c>g
A backup sequence of characters used to identify an entity
An characterisation of the variant that indicates the state or progress (e.g., confirmed, to be verified, etc.)
E.g. SNP
E.g. GRCh37
E.g. TTN

A structure found in the nucleus of human cells that is comprised of a strand of linearized double-stranded DNA plus proteins that package the DNA in a condensed coil form and regulate chromosomal function.
An extended part of a chromosome representing a term of convenience in order to hierarchically organize morphologically defined chromosome features: chromosome > arm > region > band > sub-band.

An allelic state that describes the degree of similarity between features in a 'single locus complement', within the genome of a cell or organism (i.e., whether the alleles or haplotypes that reside at the same location on paired chromosomes are the same or different).
The starting position of a sequence feature or interval. E.g. 2447955
The ending position of a sequence feature or interval. E.g. 2447955
An allele whose sequence matches what is consdiered to be the reference sequence at that location in the genome.
Any allele of a variant which is not the in the reference genome currently being studied. The alternative allele is not necessarily the minor allele.

Genetic Variation consists of deviation(s) in the nucleotide sequence of the genetic material of an individual from that typical of the group to which the individual belongs, or deviation(s) in the nucleotide sequence of the genetic material of offspring from that of its parents.
Agreement as the result of multiple results or opinions.
